Package us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.interfaces

Interface FrameVector2DBasics

  • All Superinterfaces:
    us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Clearable, FixedFrameTuple2DBasics, FixedFrameVector2DBasics, FrameChangeable, FrameTuple2DBasics, FrameTuple2DReadOnly, FrameVector2DReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Transformable, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple2D.interfaces.Tuple2DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple2D.interfaces.Tuple2DReadOnly, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple2D.interfaces.Vector2DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple2D.interfaces.Vector2DReadOnly
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FrameVector2D
    public interface FrameVector2DBasics
extends FixedFrameVector2DBasics, FrameTuple2DBasics, FrameChangeable
    Write and read interface for a 2D vector expressed in a changeable reference frame, i.e. the reference frame in which this vector is expressed can be changed.

    In addition to representing a Vector2DBasics, a ReferenceFrame is associated to a FrameVector2DBasics. This allows, for instance, to enforce, at runtime, that operations on vectors occur in the same coordinate system.

    Because a FrameVector2DBasics extends Vector2DBasics, it is compatible with methods only requiring Vector2DBasics. However, these methods do NOT assert that the operation occur in the proper coordinate system. Use this feature carefully and always prefer using methods requiring FrameVector2DBasics.

    • Method Detail

      • changeFrameAndProjectToXYPlane

        void changeFrameAndProjectToXYPlane​(ReferenceFrame desiredFrame)
        Performs a transformation of the vector such that it is expressed in a new frame desireFrame.

        Because the transformation between two reference frames is a 3D transformation, the result of transforming this vector 2D can result in a vector 3D. This method projects the result of the transformation onto the XY-plane.

        Parameters:
        desiredFrame - the reference frame in which the vector is to be expressed.
